HawsEDC stock version 1.0, 1999: LAYERS.DAT
By Thomas Gail Haws
Layers defaults file for lisp routines
Use this file to change HawsEDC layer names, colors, or linetypes.
The commands depend on the lines in this file.
If you remove any of the lines in this file or modify the key names,
the commands will use the current layer.
Format:
("Key Name" "Layer Name" "Color" "Linetype")
If the color or linetype field is left empty, the Autocad default is used.
Layer to insert multilayer or explode blocks on (usually "0")

Note about layers for PRO:
PRO can avoid labelling conflicts only if you use a consistent prefix
for all PRO layer names and a consistent suffix for all PRO text layers.
See the PROPRE and PROTXSUF layer keys.
For profile utilities, you can add new layers whose key is PRO and
the data file protyp utility name.  Eg: "PRO" and "WAT" = PROWAT
